WHO   — COLECOVISION — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — Coleco's console punched straight at the arcade: a Z80, the proven TMS9918A video chip, and a pack-in port of Donkey Kong so close to the coin-op that it sold the machine on its own. An expansion module even let it play Atari 2600 games — a bold shot at the whole market.
WHERE — the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
